[b][size=200]pandoc-bbcode-phpbb[/size][/b]

[b][size=180]Introduction[/size][/b]

This is a modified Lua script to write phpBB’s subset of BBCode via [url=http://johnmacfarlane.net/pandoc/README.html]pandoc[/url] based on the [url=https://github.com/2ion/pandoc-bbcode]original pandoc-bbcode[/url] and [url=https://github.com/anshumanb/pandoc-bbcode-phpbb]pandoc-bbcode-phpbb[/url]. The aim is to be able to output BBCode as perfectly formatted as possible with the result not necessarily being human-readable.

You can view this readme’s autogenerated BBCode [url=https://github.com/mathewv/pandoc-bbcode-phpbb/blob/master/README.bbcode]here[/url].

This script can be used used with Pandoc in the following way:

[code]pandoc -t pandoc-bbcode-phpbb.lua -o $output $input[/code]
[b][size=180]Markdown Demonstration[/size][/b]

[b][size=140]Text emphasis[/size][/b]

[i]Simple emphasis[/i], [b]strong emphasis[/b]

[b][size=140]Quoting[/size][/b]

Quotes without attribution:

[quote]This is a quotation with no author specified.[/quote]
Quotes with attribution:

[quote="Username"]This text was written by “Username”[/quote]
Though not standard in phpBB, you can also use [u]@spoiler[/u] to generate a spoiler block:

[spoiler]It was Earth all along![/spoiler]
